projects.name: Scientific Calculator
projects.description: Developed a comprehensive scientific calculator application utilizing Python and the Tkinter library. The project features a user-friendly graphical interface with support for advanced mathematical functions such as trigonometric operations, logarithms, factorials, permutations, combinations, and more.

projects.name: Product and User Management API
projects.description: Developed a scalable RESTful API using Node.js and Express.js for efficient management of product and user data. The API supports CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations on a MongoDB database, ensuring smooth handling of product and user information. Technologies used include Node.js, Express.js for the backend, and MongoDB with Mongoose for the database.

projects.name: People Counting System
projects.description: Developed a robust people counting system leveraging machine learning techniques with OpenCV and Python, utilizing the MobileNetSSD model for real-time person detection and tracking. This system efficiently handles object detection, tracking, and counting, demonstrating advanced skills in computer vision and deep learning.

projects.name: Automated Attendance System Using Face Recognition
projects.description: Developed a comprehensive automated attendance system leveraging advanced face recognition technology. Utilized Python libraries including OpenCV.
